 cameras are still rolling.\n\nGuest stars: Utkarsh Ambudkar as Pizza, [[Willie Nelson]] as himself,<ref name=\"seasonfinale\">{{cite web|url=http://www.spoilertv.com/2016/02/the-muppets-season-1-final-two-episodes.html?m=1|title=The Muppets - Season 1 Finale - Press Release *Updated*|work=SpoilerTV|last=Anop|first=Nirat|date=February 19, 2016}}</ref> [[Phil LaMarr]] as Miss Piggy's doctor  \n|LineColor       = 98FB98\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 16\n|Title           = Because... Love\n|DirectedBy      = Randall Einhorn\n|WrittenBy       = [[Scott Weinger]] & Emily Wilson\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|3|1}}\n|Viewers         = 2.73<ref name=\"1.15&1.16\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/03/02/tuesday-final-ratings-march-1-2016/|title=Tuesday Final Ratings: 'New Girl' adjusts up|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=March 2, 2016|accessdate=March 2, 2016|publisher=TV by the Numbers}}</ref>\n|ShortSummary    = Kermit and Miss Piggy struggle with the aftermath of the previous night with Kermit realizing that he still loves her, but is apprehensive. Other Muppet characters have appeared at the studio after they saw the news as Howard Tubman hooks up some acts for Rizzo and Scooter to present on ''Up Late with Miss Piggy''. Kermit flips a coin to decide at the suggestion of Rowlf. Miss Piggy believes that they are getting back together is all but confirmed. The staff try to help Kermit decide, with varying thoughts on the positives and negatives. After running into [[Jack White]], Kermit makes a decision. After finding out about the coin flip, Miss Piggy is outraged and makes up her mind. At the taping, Jack White performs \"[[You Are the Sunshine of My Life]]\" and she runs off while the staff try to encourage her to reconsider on-air. Wanting to get away, Miss Piggy is on a plane to [[Thailand]]. Kermit arrives with a calzone and the two make a final decision. What Kermit and Miss Piggy don't know is that Pepe is secretly on the plane with them.\n\nGuest star: [[Jack White]] as himself<ref name=\"seasonfinale\" />\n|LineColor       = 98FB98\n}}\n}}\n\n==Production==\n[[Bill Prady]] originated the idea to bring The Muppets back to prime-time television and enlisted [[Bob Kushell]] as co-creator and showrunner for the project, allowing Prady to concurrently continue performing his duties as executive producer on ''The Big Bang Theory'', which CBS had renewed through its tenth season, for the [[2016\u201317 United States network television schedule|2016\u201317 season]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/big-bang-theory-renewed-season-687949 |title='Big Bang Theory' Renewed Through Season 10 |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=March 12, 2014 |accessdate=May 8, 2015}}</ref> Before ABC was approached, [[Netflix]] expressed interest in co-producing the series as part of its original programming roster.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lynch|first1=Jason|title=Inside The Muppets' Decade-Long Journey Back to Prime-Time TV ABC places its biggest fall bet on Kermit and Miss Piggy|url=http://www.adweek.com/news/television/inside-muppets-decade-long-journey-back-prime-time-tv-167031|accessdate=October 1, 2015|work=Adweek|date=September 20, 2015}}</ref>\n\n''The Muppets'' was considered a \"stealth, late presentation\" in the 2015 comedy development season. After buying Prady and Kushell's pitch, ABC ordered a [[Television pilot|pilot]] script and a 10-minute proof of concept filmed presentation, which was filmed at the [[Walt Disney Studios (Burbank)|Walt Disney Studios]] in May and delivered just in time for ABC schedule consideration.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/muppet-show-reboot-abc-bill-prady-1201466006/ |title=ABC Eyes 'Muppet Show' Reboot |last=Friedlander |first=Whitney |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=April 3, 2015 |accessdate=April 3, 2015}}</ref> On May 7, 2015, ABC greenlit the series to order as an entry in the 2015\u201316 television season.<ref>{{cite web |author=The Futon Critic Staff |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2015/05/07/development-update-thursday-may-7-three-new-comedies-heading-to-series-at-abc-905225/11331/ |title=Development Update: Thursday, May 7\u2014Three New Comedies Heading to Series at ABC |publisher=[[The Futon Critic]] |date=May 7, 2015 |accessdate=May 7, 2015}}</ref> The pitch presentation, which was first screened to the public on July 11, 2015, at [[San Diego Comic-Con International|Comic-Con]] to  an overwhelmingly positive response, was released online on July 21, 2015.<ref name=\"THRComicCon\">{{cite web|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|title=Comic-Con: 'Muppets' Steal the Spotlight, Get Standing Ovation|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/comic-con-2015-muppets-808139|accessdate=July 12, 2015|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=July 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Lowe|first=Kinsey|date=July 21, 2015|title='The Muppets' Pilot Pitch: What Was Screened at Comic Con|url=http://deadline.com/2015/07/the-muppets-abc-comic-con-1201483035/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=July 22, 2015}}</ref> In regards to what Muppet characters to include, producers decided to omit extremely anthropomorphic characters such as \"talking vegetables and dancing chickens\".<ref name=NYTProd>{{cite web|last=Barnes|first=Brooks|title=On 'The Muppets', Miss Piggy Has a Talk Show and a Chatty Staff|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/13/arts/television/on-the-muppets-miss-piggy-has-a-talk-show-and-a-chatty-staff.html|accessdate=September 7, 2015|work=The New York Times|date=September 7, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe series was shot at Stages 6 and 7 of the Walt Disney Studios lot in [[Burbank, California]] and on-location throughout [[Los Angeles]].{{citation needed|date=September 2015}} Sets must be raised four and a half feet so that the Muppet performers will have room to operate the characters, and all sets have platforms which can be moved.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://decoy.tvpassport.com/news/back-prime-time-abc-raises-curtain-famous-puppet-crew-muppets?subid=national-00001|title=Back in prime time: ABC raises the curtain on the famous puppet crew in 'The Muppets'|last=Brewer|first=Kyla|work=TV Media|accessdate=September 24, 2015}}</ref> ''The Muppets'' received a full 16-episode season from ABC on October 29, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last=Littleton|first=Cynthia|title=ABC Gives Full Season Order to 'The Muppets' with Three More Episodes|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/muppets-full-season-pickup-abc-1201630120/|accessdate=October 30, 2015|work=Variety|date=October 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn early November 2015, it was announced that Kushell was leaving the series, with Kristen Newman in talks to replace him. The move was reportedly part of a creative overhaul of the series, which saw the final six episodes of the first season act as a relaunch of the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/11/the-muppets-showrunner-bob-kushell-exit-kristin-newman-reboot-1201606360/|title='The Muppets' Showrunner Bob Kushell Exits As Series Heads For Reboot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=November 4, 2015|accessdate=November 5, 2015}}</ref> Newman began work during production of the tenth episode, which involved her rewriting the Miss Piggy-Kermit scenes to \"bring [their] connection back... that was being walked away from completely\" in the early episodes. Newman also hoped to introduce more [[Serial (radio and television)|serialized]] elements to the series.<ref name=\"THRNewman\" /> However, ABC cancelled ''The Muppets'' on May 12, 2016 after one season.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Holloway|first1=Daniel|title=\u2018The Muppets\u2019 Cancelled by ABC|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/the-muppets-cancelled-by-abc-1201773341/|accessdate=May 13, 2016|work=Variety|date=May 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAfter being dismissed from The Muppets performer troupe in 2016, [[Steve Whitmire]] talked to the media about how he provided notes on scripts for the series, saying that the longtime performers know the characters best. He cited the episode \"Little Green Lie\" as an example of how he felt the characters were being scripted wrong, noting: \n{{Quote|I think that as Robin came to Kermit, he would say 'things happen, people go their separate ways, but that doesn't mean we don't care about you.' Kermit is too compassionate to lie to him to spare his feelings.<ref name=\"THR-conduct\">{{cite news|last1=Parker|first1=Ryan|title=Disney Says It Fired Kermit the Frog Actor Over \"Unacceptable Business Conduct\"|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-says-fired-kermit-frog-actor-unacceptable-business-conduct-1021701|accessdate=19 July 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=17 July 2017}}</ref>}}\n\n==Broadcast==\n''The Muppets'' premiered on September 22, 2015 on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/abc-sets-fall-premiere-dates-for-muppets-wicked-city-more-1201516557/ |title=ABC Sets Fall Premiere Dates for 'Muppets,' 'Wicked City,' 'TGIT' & More |last=Friedlander |first=Whitney |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=June 10, 2015 |accessdate=June 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=The Muppets |title=THIS JUST IN!!! Our new series, The Muppets ABC will premiere on Tuesday, September 22nd at 8:00 pm! It's primetime to light the lights! |publisher=[[Facebook]] |url=https://www.facebook.com/muppets/photos/a.10150162022752035.298754.177534557034/10152813627637035/?type=1&theater |accessdate=June 10, 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610203317/https://www.facebook.com/muppets/photos/a.10150162022752035.298754.177534557034/10152813627637035/?type=1&theater |archivedate=June 10, 2015 |date=June 10, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> It was broadcast on [[Sky 1]] in the UK, starting Monday October 19, 2015.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Plunkett |first1=John |title=The Muppets Mockumentary TV Series to Air on Sky 1 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jul/09/the-muppets-mockumentary-tv-series-sky-1 |accessdate=July 11, 2015 |work=[[The Guardian]] |location=London |date=July 9, 2015}}</ref> The series was also acquired by the [[Seven Network]] in Australia<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://tvtonight.com.au/2015/09/the-muppets-set-for-seven.html|title=The Muppets set for Seven |date=September 2, 2015|accessdate=September 4, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/10/the-muppets-soon-on-seven.html|title=The Muppets \"soon\" on Seven|date=October 1, 2015|accessdate=October 1, 2015}}</ref> and premiered on December 29, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/12/airdate-the-muppets.html|title=Airdate: The Muppets |date=8 December 2015|accessdate=8 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical reception===\nOn the review aggregate website [[Metacritic]], ''The Muppets'' has a metascore of 62 out of 100, based on 31 reviews, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/the-muppets-2015|title=The Muppets Reviews|publisher=Metacritic.com}}</ref> On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series has a rating of 63%, based on 57 reviews, with an average rating of 6.46/10. The site's critical consensus reads: \"''The Muppets'' brings new energy to a beloved franchise\u2014and although longtime fans may be taken aback by the show's adult mockumentary approach, the classic characters retain their essential spirit.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/the-muppets/s01/ |title=The Muppets: Season 1 |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=June 27, 2019}}</ref> ''[[The Washington Post]]''{{'}}s Hank Stuever complimented the series, calling it \"a smart and often witty update to the Muppet brand,\" giving it a \"B\".<ref name=\"Washington Post Fall TV Preview\">{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/entertainment/2015-fall-tv-preview/ |title=Fall TV Preview 2015 |first=Hank |last=Stuever |date=September 16, 2015 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=September 23, 2015}}</ref> Merrill Barr of ''[[Forbes]]'' wrote a negative review, stating, \"By taking these creatures and turning them into 'real' people, the only way to make them funny becomes having them do outlandish things. The only problem is they're inherently outlandish just by existing, so everything they do just feels tame and lifeless by comparison.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/merrillbarr/2015/09/16/the-muppets-tv-show-review/|title='The Muppets' Review: A Joyless Excursion Made For Adult Fans That Lacks What Made Them Fans At All|first=Merrill|last=Barr|work=Forbes|date=September 16, 2015|accessdate=September 16, 2015}}</ref> Dominic Patten of ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' negatively compared the series to ''[[Studio 60 on the Sunset Strip]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nBbUkCbOX6s|title='The Muppets' on ABC - TV Review|author=Deadline Hollywood|work=YouTube|date=September 16, 2015|accessdate=September 16, 2015}}</ref> Brian Lowry of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' gave a more mixed reaction, calling it \"something of a mixed bag\", praising the humor, but criticizing the subplot of Fozzie dating a human woman.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/reviews/the-muppets-review-abc-comedy-1201595069/|title=The Muppets: TV Review|first=Brian|last=Lowry|work=Variety|date=September 17, 2015|accessdate=September 17, 2015}}</ref> On the other hand, [[Dorothy Rabinowitz]] of ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' was more positive toward the series. She wrote, \"As soon as you begin watching the new ''Muppets'' the question arises\u2014how come no one thought of this before? So perfect is the idea of a late-night talk show called ''Up Late with Miss Piggy'' one has to wonder.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-muppets-review-all-grown-up-1442529605|title='The Muppets' Review: All Grown Up|first=Dorothy|last=Rabinowitz|work=The Wall Street Journal|date=September 17, 2015|accessdate=September 17, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Criticism=== \nThe group [[One Million Moms]], an offshoot of the [[American Family Association]], began protesting ''The Muppets'', citing it as \"unsuitable for family viewing\", and calling for [[boycotts]] against it immediately after ABC picked it up, long before the series debuted.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/the-muppets-are-perverted-and-ruined-according-to-one-million-moms/|title='The Muppets' Slammed as 'Perverted' and 'Ruined' by One Million Moms Advocacy Group|last=Verhoeven|first=Beatrice|work=The Wrap|date=September 23, 2015|accessdate=September 26, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://onemillionmoms.com/current-campaigns/warning-the-new-muppets-is-not-family-friendly/|title=Warning! The New 'Muppets' is Not Family-Friendly|work=OneMillionMoms.com|date=September 25, 2015|accessdate=September 25, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2015-10-18/us-pressure-group-new-muppets-show-is-perverted/|title=US pressure group calls for 'perverted' Muppets show to be banned|work=ITV News|date=October 18, 2015|accessdate=October 18, 2015}}</ref> ''The Muppets'' later parodied One Million Moms' critique in their twelfth episode, \"A Tail of Two Piggies\", as the One Million Angry Parents Association represented by three protesters.<ref>source: \"A Tail of Two Piggies\" airdate February 9, 2016</ref>{{third-party inline|date=December 2016}}\n\nThe [[Parents Television Council]] also criticized the series for not meeting \"family viewing\" guidelines and suggested a [[boycott]], based on the mockumentary format of the series including mentions of plastic surgery, \"inside\" business language being used in a crude manner, and the Muppets in a bar consuming alcoholic beverages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://w2.parentstv.org/Main/News/Detail.aspx?docID=3296|title=New PTC Research Finds ABC's The Muppets Exposes Kids to Adult-Themed Content Every 3 Minutes|last=Oliver|first=Kelley|work=Parents Television Council|date=October 20, 2015|accessdate=October 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Accolades ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Award\n!Category\n!Recipients and nominees\n!Result\n|-\n|[[Kids' Choice Awards]]\n|Favorite Family TV Show<ref>{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=Zach|title=Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards 2016 Winners List|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/748176/nickelodeon-kids-choice-awards-2016-winners-list|accessdate=August 27, 2016|work=E News|date=March 12, 2016}}</ref>\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Art Direction for a Contemporary Program (Half hour or less)|Outstanding Art Direction for a Contemporary Program (Half Hour or Less)]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Abrams|first1=Natalie|title=Emmys 2016: Minority Report, The Muppets, and other post-cancellation nominations|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/07/14/emmy-nominations-shows-canceled|accessdate=July 22, 2016|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=July 14, 2016}}</ref>\n|Denise Ann Pizzini, Production Designer; Don Diers, Set Decorator\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n===Ratings===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;width:99%\"\n|-\n! No.\n! Title\n! Air date\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | [[Nielsen ratings|Rating/share]]<br/>(18\u201349)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Viewers<br/>(millions)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | [[Digital video recorder|DVR]]<br/>(18\u201349)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | DVR viewers<br/>(millions)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Total<br/>(18\u201349)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Total viewers<br/>(millions)\n|-\n| 1\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | \"[[#ep1|Pig Girls Don't Cry (Pilot)]]\"\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{Start date|2015|9|22}}\n| 2.9/10\n| 9.01<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| 1.1\n| 2.68\n| 4.0\n| 11.69<ref>{{c