n|date=February 2013\n}}\n'''Starooskolsky District''' ({{lang-ru|\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u0301\u043d}}) is an administrative district ([[raion]]), one of the [[administrative divisions of Belgorod Oblast|twenty-one]] in [[Belgorod Oblast]], [[Russia]].<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\">Law #248</ref> It is located in the north of the [[oblast]].<!-- and borders with [[ District]] in the north, [[ District]] in the east, [[ District]] in the south, and [[ District]] in the west.--> The area of the district is {{convert|1694|km2|sp=us}}.<ref name='about'>{{cite web|title=General Information|url=https://belregion.ru/region/?ELEMENT_ID=266|publisher=Starooskolsky District|language=russian|access-date=January 11, 2017}}</ref> Its [[administrative center]] is the [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|city]] of [[Stary Oskol]]<ref name=\"OKATO\">{{OKATO reference|14 252}}</ref> (which is not administratively a part of the district).<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\" /> Population: {{ru-census2010|35,457|;}} 35,063 ([[Russian Census (2002)|2002 Census]]);<ref name=\"2002Census\">{{ru-pop-ref|2002Census}}</ref> {{su-census1989|35,266|.}}\n\n==Administrative and municipal status==\nWithin the [[subdivisions of Russia#Administrative divisions|framework of administrative divisions]], Starooskolsky District is one of the [[administrative divisions of Belgorod Oblast|twenty-one]] in the oblast.<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\" /> The city of [[Stary Oskol]] serves as its [[administrative center]],<ref name=\"OKATO\" /> despite being incorporated separately as a [[city of federal subject significance|town of oblast significance]]\u2014an administrative unit with the status equal to that of the districts.<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\" />\n\nAs a [[subdivisions of Russia#Municipal divisions|municipal division]], the territory of the district and the territory of the city of oblast significance of Stary Oskol are incorporated together as [[Starooskolsky Urban Okrug]].<ref name=\"BelgorodO_mun\">Law #159</ref>\n\n==References==\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Sources===\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|bel|adm|law}}\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|bel|adm|list|starooskolsky}}\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|bel|mun|list}}\n\n{{Belgorod Oblast}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2013}}\n\n[[Category:Districts of Belgorod Oblast]]\n\n__NOTOC__\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Russian district\n|en_name=Starooskolsky District\n|ru_name=\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\n|image_map={{Russia district OSM map}}\n|map_caption=Location of Starooskolsky District in Belgorod Oblast\n|image_view=\u0421.\u041e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043b,\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043c \u0420\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430.JPG\n|image_caption=Church of the Nativity\n|coordinates = {{coord|51.307|N|37.838|E|type:adm2nd_region:RU|display=inline,title}}\n|latm\n|lats\n|longm\n|longs\n|image_flag=Flag of Stary Oskol (Belgorod oblast).png\n|flag_caption\n|image_coa=Coat of Arms of Stary Oskol (Belgorod oblast).png\n|coa_caption\n|anthem\n|anthem_ref\n|holiday\n|holiday_ref\n|federal_subject=[[Belgorod Oblast]]\n|federal_subject_ref=<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\" />\n|adm_data_as_of=June 2008\n|adm_ctr_type=[[types of inhabited localities in Russia|city]]\n|adm_ctr_name=[[Stary Oskol]]\n|adm_ctr_ref=<ref name=\"OKATO\" />\n|no_of_rural_localities=78\n|counts_ref=<ref name=\"BelgorodOStarooskolskyD_adm\">Resolution #P/21-21-4</ref>\n|mun_data_as_of=October 2012\n|mun_formation1=[[Starooskolsky Urban Okrug]]\n|mun_formation1_ref=<ref name=\"BelgorodO_mun\" />\n|mun_formation1_leader_title=\n|mun_formation1_leader_title_ref=\n|mun_formation1_leader_name=\n|mun_formation1_leader_name_ref=\n|mun_formation1_representative_body=\n|mun_formation1_representative_body_ref=\n|area_of_what\n|area_as_of\n|area_km2=1694\n|area_km2_ref=<ref name=\"about\"/>\n|pop_2010census=35457\n|urban_pop_2010census=0%\n|rural_pop_2010census=100%\n|pop_2010_census_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\" />\n|pop_latest=\n|pop_latest_date=\n|pop_latest_ref=\n|established_date=\n|established_date_ref=\n|prev_name1\n|prev_name1_date\n|prev_name1_ref\n|newspaper=\n|newspaper_ref=\n|website=https://belregion.ru/region/?ELEMENT_ID=266\n|website_ref\n|commonscat=\n|date=February 2013\n}}\n'''Starooskolsky District''' ({{lang-ru|\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043e\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u0301\u043d}}) is an administrative district ([[raion]]), one of the [[administrative divisions of Belgorod Oblast|twenty-one]] in [[Belgorod Oblast]], [[Russia]].<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\">Law #248</ref> It is located in the north of the [[oblast]].<!-- and borders with [[ District]] in the north, [[ District]] in the east, [[ District]] in the south, and [[ District]] in the west.--> The area of the district is {{convert|1694|km2|sp=us}}<ref name='about'>{{cite web|title=General Information|url=https://belregion.ru/region/?ELEMENT_ID=266|publisher=Starooskolsky District|language=russian|access-date=January 11, 2017}}</ref>. Its [[administrative center]] is the [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|city]] of [[Stary Oskol]]<ref name=\"OKATO\">{{OKATO reference|14 252}}</ref> (which is not administratively a part of the district).<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\" /> Population: {{ru-census2010|35,457|;}} 35,063 ([[Russian Census (2002)|2002 Census]]);<ref name=\"2002Census\">{{ru-pop-ref|2002Census}}</ref> {{su-census1989|35,266|.}}\n\n==Administrative and municipal status==\nWithin the [[subdivisions of Russia#Administrative divisions|framework of administrative divisions]], Starooskolsky District is one of the [[administrative divisions of Belgorod Oblast|twenty-one]] in the oblast.<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\" /> The city of [[Stary Oskol]] serves as its [[administrative center]],<ref name=\"OKATO\" /> despite being incorporated separately as a [[city of federal subject significance|town of oblast significance]]\u2014an administrative unit with the status equal to that of the districts.<ref name=\"BelgorodO_adm\" />\n\nAs a [[subdivisions of Russia#Municipal divisions|municipal division]], the territory of the district and the territory of the city of oblast significance of Stary Oskol are incorporated together as [[Starooskolsky Urban Okrug]].<ref name=\"BelgorodO_mun\">Law #159</ref>\n\n==References==\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Sources===\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|bel|adm|law}}\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|bel|adm|list|starooskolsky}}\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|bel|mun|list}}\n\n{{Belgorod Oblast}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2013}}\n\n[[Category:Districts of Belgorod Oblast]]\n\n__NOTOC__\n", "name_user": "DannyS712", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixing the location of periods / full stops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Starooskolsky_District"}
